title: Date of the contract
explanation: Phrase 'dated as of September 12, 2008'.

title: Party A
explanation: Header shows both labels but misaligned; provisions (e.g., Credit Support Default, Cross Default apply to Party A) indicate the bank is Party A.

title: party_B
value: World Financial Network Credit Card Master Note Trust
explanation: Other named counterparty in the header; Party B inferred given Party A aligns with the bank in the provisions.

title: Specified entity Party A
explanation: Part 1(a): “Specified Entity shall not apply to Party A or Party B.”

title: Specified entity Party B
explanation: Part 1(a): “Specified Entity shall not apply to Party A or Party B.”

title: Specified transaction scope
explanation: No change to Section 14 definition of Specified Transaction; only Section 5(a)(v) non-applicability stated (Part 1(e)).

title: Cross default applicable parties
explanation: Part 1(f): Cross Default applies to Party A and will not apply to Party B.

title: Specified indebtness includes borrowed_money
explanation: Part 1(f) (following paragraph): Specified Indebtedness has the meaning in Section 14 (standard definition is borrowed money).

title: Specified indebtness excludes deposits
explanation: Part 1(f) (following paragraph): deposits received in ordinary banking business are excluded.

title: amount for Party A
explanation: Part 1(f) (following paragraph): Threshold Amount is 3% of total shareholders’ equity (percentage-based, no fixed amount).

title: currency for Party A
explanation: Threshold for Party A set as a percentage, not a currency amount.

title: percentage for Party A
explanation: Part 1(f) (following paragraph): “3% of its total shareholders equity.”

title: percentage reference for Party A
explanation: Reference is to “total shareholders’ equity.”

title: amount for Party B
explanation: No Threshold Amount specified for Party B.

title: currency for Party B
explanation: No Threshold Amount specified for Party B.

title: percentage for Party B
explanation: No Threshold Amount specified for Party B.

title: percentage reference for Party B
explanation: No Threshold Amount specified for Party B.

title: Credit Event Upon Merger  applicable parties
explanation: Part 1(k): Credit Event Upon Merger will not apply to Party A or Party B.

title: Automatic Early Termination  applicable parties
explanation: Part 1(l): Automatic Early Termination will not apply to Party A or Party B.

title: Termination Currency
explanation: Part 1(m): “Termination Currency means United States Dollars.”

title: Email for notices for Party A
explanation: Part 4(b)(i): Notice details list address/phone/fax but no email for Party A.

title: Email for notices for Party B
explanation: Part 4(b)(ii): Notice details list address/phone/fax but no email for Party B.

title: Process agent for party A
explanation: Part 4(h): Party A appoints a Process Agent.

title: Name of process agent for party A
explanation: Part 4(h): “Barclays Capital” named as Process Agent for Party A.

title: Address of process agent for party A
value: 200 Park Avenue, New York, NY 10166, Attn: Legal Department
explanation: Part 4(h): Address provided for Party A’s Process Agent.

title: Process agent for party B
explanation: Part 4(h): “Party B appoints as its Process Agent… Not applicable.”

title: Name of process agent for party B
explanation: Process agent not applicable for Party B.

title: Address of process agent for party B
explanation: Process agent not applicable for Party B.

title: Party A is a Multibranch party
explanation: Part 4(d)(ii)(1): Party A is a Multibranch Party.

title: Party A offices
explanation: Part 4(d)(ii)(1): Party A may act through its London and New York Offices.

title: Party B is a Multibranch party
explanation: Part 4(d)(ii)(2): Party B is not a Multibranch Party.

title: Party B offices
explanation: Party B is not a Multibranch Party.

title: Party for calculation agent
explanation: Part 4(e): Calculation Agent is Party A (with fallback to a designee by Party B upon Party A default).

title: Governing Law
explanation: Part 4(a): Governed by the laws of the State of New York.
